cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on the problem of adversarial attacks on neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper proposes a method for certifying the robustness of neural networks, which involves solving a semidefinite program, a technique that is commonly used in the field of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper also discusses the optimization of the certificate along with the network parameters, which is a topic that falls under the category of neural network optimization (cs.NE).
